    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12 max-w-4xl">
      <h2>Why merchants leave Rejoiner</h2>
      <p>For Rejoiner alternatives, revenue per send economics separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Arena Energy (sports nutrition, $130k/mo) runs flavor drop paired with athlete collab — sms to gym-bag segment. Operating lesson: Free shaker only in email; SMS was drop timing only. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, broadcast frequency caps separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Loom & Frame (limited art prints, $44k/mo) runs edition size disclosed upfront; sms to 3+ order collectors when 50% edition sold. Operating lesson: Scarcity SMS at halfway sell-through converted 2.3x better than launch blast. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, waitlist priority queues separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Driftwood Surf Co (seasonal boardshort drops, $88k/mo) runs summer drop calendar tied to swell forecast content in sequenzy. Operating lesson: Restock SMS to waitlist beat full-list restock announcement. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, scarcity timing not launch blasts separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Noir Collective (flash-sale streetwear, $240k/mo) runs thursday 6pm drop calendar with vip sms 2 hours early. Operating lesson: Cut broadcast frequency from 4x/week to 2x/week — revenue per send rose 31%. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, holdout testing before scale separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. SoleDrop ATX (limited sneaker releases, $180k/mo) runs size-run sell-through in 11 minutes with waitlist priority queue. Operating lesson: VIP segment got early link; general list email after 70% inventory moved — unsubscribes dropped 40%. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, margin after incentive math separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Festival Threads Co (tour merch, $95k/mo seasonal) runs city-specific tour date campaigns geo-segmented by venue timezone. Operating lesson: Campaign calendar tied to tour routing — 3 texts per city max. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify card mb-12 max-w-4xl">
      <h2>Migration playbook</h2>
      <p>For Rejoiner alternatives, quarterly calendar planning separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Vinyl Vault Records (collector drops, $62k/mo) runs pressing quantity disclosed upfront; sms only to waitlist plus 2+ order collectors. Operating lesson: Segment-by-value: collectors with $400+ LTV get first access. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, drop orchestration with inventory truth separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Bloom & Wick (candle gifting, $110k/mo) runs holiday campaign calendar built in august with teaser and shipping deadline tiers. Operating lesson: Gift segments got bundle SMS; self-purchase segment got scent education email via Sequenzy. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, bargain-hunter isolation from VIP access separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Peak Trail Gear (outdoor flash sales, $155k/mo) runs end-of-season clearance only to bargain-sensitive rfm quartile. Operating lesson: Holdout test proved 15% off to full-price loyalists destroyed margin. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, Sequenzy email depth beside Postscript SMS separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Sauce Lab (limited hot sauce drops, $48k/mo) runs batch-number scarcity campaigns — sms when 200 bottles left. Operating lesson: Restraint: one launch SMS plus one scarcity SMS per drop. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, Attentive enterprise governance at scale separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Ember Ceramics (maker pottery drops, $38k/mo) runs waitlist of 4,200 for 80-piece kiln with fulfillment order preserved. Operating lesson: Sequenzy email carried maker story; Postscript sent single VIP access text. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p><p>For Rejoiner alternatives, campaign calendar discipline separates welcome campaign moments from list fatigue. Ridge Run Coffee (subscription plus flash offers, $72k/mo) runs subscribers suppressed from flash promos; flash offers only to non-subscriber engaged segment. Operating lesson: Campaign collision audit caught flash SMS hitting active subscribers. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution on shopifysmsmarketingapps.com. Attentive ranks #2 for enterprise promotional calendars. Sequenzy is the lifecycle email layer — welcome, education, winback, replenishment planning beside dedicated text senders.</p>
